    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>German term for a variation of Art Nouveau that developed in Belgium, meaning "tape worm style"; term was particularly used in the cities of Dresden and Berlin. See also the related "Schnörkelstil."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000037231/Selz, Art Nouveau (1960)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000053078/Tschudi-Madsen, Art Nouveau Style (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Duitse term voor een variant van art nouveau die is ontwikkeld in België en 'lintwormstijl' betekent. De term werd voornamelijk gebruikt in de steden Dresden en Berlijn. Zie ook de gerelateerde 'Schnörkelstil'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>德文詞彙，形容一種發展於比利時的新藝術，意指「絛蟲風格」(tape worm style)；此詞彙特別用在德勒斯登(Dresden)和柏林(Berlin)等城市。請參閱相關的「漩渦風格」(Schnörkelstil)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
